{
  "stem": "1033.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember my grandfather used to go to a place called [NON-ENGLISH], the place where my mother was eventually hospitalized.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Not too often, maybe five times a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he used to come back with little red hats for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was the-- what the young Hungarian soldiers wore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember at school, the-- in fact the sons of the teacher who was teaching me, kept shouting at me, shouting, Jewish [HUNGARIAN]-- which means, look, what a joke, a Jewish soldier.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- I just-- I just ran.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It seems to me so much of my life-- and I find that most regrettable-- had been lived in flight.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I do notice various kinds of flight patterns right now, right here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You don't have to be Jewish to know what I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And anti-Semitism, of course, was more than registered for me as-- as my life unfolded, albeit that it is a happy kind of finish, for which I am profoundly grateful.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in the orphanage, we heard stories.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We heard people running away from Czechoslovakia, from Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had some kids in the orphanage-- smf we were so cruel, because these kids didn't speak Hungarian, they spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they used to say [YIDDISH]-- and-- which means where are you from?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we used to call them 'Finns' among ourselves-- which is an awful thing to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So just as kids had been cruel with me, when I spoke Hungarian with a funny dialect, I didn't give a second thought to do this to some other kids who were really had enough on their plates.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, just three months ago, I met one of them in Israel in Ramot Naftali, whose wife is coming in a couple of months.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
